# Mobile APK — clean build only

When the user asks to build an APK (including Hebrew: APK, אפליקציה, קלין בילד):

## Required workflow

**Do not** run bare `flutter clean` + `flutter build apk` without restoring web.

Use **only** this sequence (repo root):

```powershell
.\mobile\scripts\build_apk_clean.ps1
```

Or run the steps manually in order:

```powershell
cd mobile
flutter clean
flutter pub get
flutter build apk --release
cd ..
git restore mobile/build/web
```

## Why

`mobile/build/web` is **tracked in Git** for Render static deploy. `flutter clean` deletes it and Git shows dozens of deleted files. `git restore mobile/build/web` restores the committed web bundle without affecting the APK.

## Do not

- Skip `git restore mobile/build/web` after clean
- Commit deleted or modified `mobile/build/web` as part of an APK-only task
- Change `.gitignore` or Render config unless the user explicitly requests web-deploy migration
- Run `flutter build web` unless the user also wants to update the Render web bundle

## Output

Report APK path: `mobile/build/app/outputs/flutter-apk/app-release.apk`

If the user changed mobile UI and needs Render web updated, use option B separately: `flutter build web` then commit `mobile/build/web` intentionally.
